OL,7,F"My little boy died at 17 because
OL,8,Fsomeone thought it was all right to
OL,9,Fput a knife into when we were told
OL,10,Fthat he was gonna die and we were
OL,11,Fgonna have to switch off his life
OL,12,Fsupport, I made Charlie a promise.
OL,14,F"I said, I promise you I will spend
OL,15,Fthe rest of my life educating young
OL,16,Fgroups of people about the dangers of
OL,17,Fknife crime.
OL,19,F"You will have a legacy, son, because
OL,20,Fyou're not old enough to have built
OL,21,Fyour own."
